<subSubSection id="21C4BAC2C6181B2DFF6CFE4EFDEEFE31" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="6961E949C6181B2DFF6CFE4EFDEEFE31" blockId="30.[151,1436,215,492]" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6181B2DFF6CFE4EFEBEFE5D" bold="true" box="[199,315,360,384]" inLineHeading="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" reason="1">Remarks.</emphasis>
Persian 
<collectingRegion id="AB1A27ABC6181B2DFE30FE41FE4BFEA2" box="[411,462,359,383]" country="Papua New Guinea" name="Gulf" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Gulf</collectingRegion>
specimens are fully agreeing with the description and single photo provided by 
<bibRefCitation id="0D4F94B8C6181B2DFAFFFE41FED9FE79" author="Nobili, G." pageId="30" pageNumber="31" pagination="1 - 347" refId="ref51435" refString="Nobili, G. (1906 b) Faune carcinologique de la Mer Rouge. Decapodes et Stomatopodes. Annales des Sciences naturelles, (Zoologie), (9) 4, 1 - 347, figs. 1 - 12, pls. 1 - 11." type="journal article" year="1906">Nobili (1906b: 155–157</bibRefCitation>
, pl. 9, fig. 2). The general characteristics of this species look to be very similar to the genus 
<taxonomicName id="AEDE92CAC6181B2DFF3CFE96FE04FE1A" authority="Leach, 1817" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[151,385,431,456]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Euphorbiaceae" genus="Philyra" kingdom="Plantae" order="Malpighiales" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6181B2DFF3CFE96FF6EFE15" box="[151,235,432,456]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Philyra</emphasis>
Leach, 1817
</taxonomicName>
, rather than the genus 
<taxonomicName id="AEDE92CAC6181B2DFD2AFE96FCDEFE1A" authority="Leach 1817" authorityName="Leach" authorityYear="1817" box="[641,859,431,456]" class="Malacostraca" family="Leucosiidae" genus="Ebalia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Decapoda" pageId="30" pageNumber="31" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="5BAA355BC6181B2DFD2AFE96FD4EFE15" box="[641,715,432,456]" italics="true" pageId="30" pageNumber="31">Ebalia</emphasis>
Leach 1817
</taxonomicName>
. An overall revision of the latter genus needs to be done using modern taxonomic characters.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
